<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-17T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-17T14:00:00-05:00" n="951" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d951">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/8201</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Blocker</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Eagle Pass, Tex</hi></placeName>., <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-17T13:00:00-06:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1916, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s November 6, 5 p.m. Called on Mexican authorities this
                            morning and impressed upon them the extreme necessity of <pb facs="0754" n="678" xml:id="pg_678"/> receiving definite information of
                            Americans at Parral. In interview a message was shown me from General
                            Murguia dated Escalon advising his capture that place after severe
                            fighting on Tuesday and that fifteen hundred Villistas defending the
                            town had fallen back toward Jiminez. Authorities express doubt that
                            Murguia will be able to obtain definite information until the capture of
                            the town, but have sent urgent telegrams to him on the subject. I have
                            also telegraphed British Vice Consul at Torreon to do all possible and
                            wire results immediately.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blocker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>